@conference{Feng2025,
 abbrev_source_title = {Proc. Des. Autom. Test Eur. DATE},
 abstract = {© 2025 EDAA.Recent research observed that pairwise query is practical enough in real-world streaming graph analytics. Given a pair of distinct vertices, existing approaches coalesce or prune vertex activations to decrease computations. However, they still suffer from severe invalid computations because they ignore contribution variations in graph updates, hindering performance improvement. In this work, we propose to enhance pairwise analytics by taking updates contributions into account. We first identify that graph updates from one batch have a distinct impact on query results and experience obvious diverse computation overheads. We then introduce CISGraph, a novel Contribution-driven pairwise accelerator with valuable updates Identification and Scheduling. Specifically, inspired by triangle inequality, CIS-Graph categorizes graph updates into three levels according to contributions, prioritizes valuable updates, delays possible-valuable updates, and drops useless updates to eliminate wasteful computations. As far as we know, CISGraph is the first hardware accelerator that supports efficient pairwise queries on streaming graphs. Experimental results show that CISGraph substantially outperforms state-of-the-art streaming graph processing systems by 25 x on average in response time.},
