 abstract = {© 2025 EDAA.ReRAM-based Processor-In-Memory (PIM) architectures have demonstrated their ability to accelerate the matrix multiplication performed by the Transformer. However, these approaches often shift the performance bottleneck from the attention mechanism to the softmax computation. Moreover, data sharding, commonly employed for acceleration, hinters the Transformer's ability to find global softmax value. This paper proposes SegTransformer, a ReRAM-based PIM accelerator that improves softmax performance with high accuracy through segmentation techniques. Experimental results indicate that the SegTransformer significantly outperforms state-of-the-art Transformer accelerators.},
