 abstract = {© 2025 EDAA.This paper proposes a novel machine learning-driven rewriting algorithm to optimize And-Inverter Graphs (AIGs) for refining combinational logic prior to technology mapping. The algorithm, called i Rw, iteratively extracts subcircuits in AIGs and replaces them with more streamlined implementations. These subcircuits are identified using an original extraction algorithm, while the compact implementations are produced through rewriting techniques guided by a machine learning model. This approach efficiently enables the generation of logically equivalent subcircuits with minimal overhead. Experiments on benchmark circuits indicate that the proposed methodology outperforms state-of-the-art AIG rewriting techniques in both quality and runtime.},
